<subSubSection lastPageId="34" lastPageNumber="417" pageId="33" pageNumber="416" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="33.[163,1070,1150,1195]" box="[208,289,1175,1195]" pageId="33" pageNumber="416">BMNH).</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="33.[163,1071,1208,1594]" pageId="33" pageNumber="416">
R e c o g n i t i o n The female of 
<taxonomicName box="[555,800,1208,1229]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Ammophila" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="33" pageNumber="416" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="brevipennis">
<emphasis box="[555,800,1208,1229]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="416">Ammophila brevipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a black gastral apex without a metallic shine, the supra-antennal lamellate projection absent and the episternal sulcus extending to the anteroventral margin of the pleuron, the mesothoracic venter not prominent anteriorly. It has the clypeus free margin rounded, without a distinct median lobe, and a red petiole. The propodeal enclosure is rugose and covered with appressed silvery setae along midline. The female of 
<taxonomicName box="[623,743,1348,1370]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Ammophila" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="33" pageNumber="416" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="assimilis">
<emphasis box="[623,743,1348,1370]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="416">A. assimilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName box="[890,1040,1348,1370]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Ammophila" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="33" pageNumber="416" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="brevipennis">
<emphasis box="[890,1040,1348,1370]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="416">A. brevipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having the clypeus with a distinct median lobe delimited laterally by a small angle (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figs 55-65" captionStartId="133.[163,203,1431,1451]" captionTargetBox="[163,1069,204,1407]" captionTargetId="figure-1@133.[163,1070,204,1411]" captionTargetPageId="133" captionText="Figs 55-65: clypeus of female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5341146" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5341146/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="416">Fig. 57</figureCitation>
) and an all all black petiole. The female of 
<taxonomicName box="[641,759,1405,1426]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Ammophila" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="33" pageNumber="416" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="punctata">
<emphasis box="[641,759,1405,1426]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="416">A. punctata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName box="[897,1044,1404,1426]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Ammophila" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="33" pageNumber="416" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="brevipennis">
<emphasis box="[897,1044,1404,1426]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="416">A. brevipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having a scutum densely and coarsely punctate (punctures 0-1 diameter apart), the mesopleuron punctate as the scutum, the clypeus with a distinct median lobe (
<figureCitation box="[986,1063,1460,1482]" captionStart="Figs 55-65" captionStartId="133.[163,203,1431,1451]" captionTargetBox="[163,1069,204,1407]" captionTargetId="figure-1@133.[163,1070,204,1411]" captionTargetPageId="133" captionText="Figs 55-65: clypeus of female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5341146" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5341146/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="416">Fig. 60</figureCitation>
) and a black petiole (
<taxonomicName box="[376,525,1488,1510]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Ammophila" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="33" pageNumber="416" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="brevipennis">
<emphasis box="[376,525,1488,1510]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="416">A. brevipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the scutum sparsely and finely punctate and the mesopleuron dull and punctato-rugose). The female of 
<taxonomicName box="[768,893,1516,1538]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Ammophila" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="33" pageNumber="416" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sabulosa">
<emphasis box="[768,893,1516,1538]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="416">A. sabulosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Ammophila" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="33" pageNumber="416" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="brevipennis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="416">A. brevipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having the gastral apex with metallic shine, the propodeal enclosure all covered with erect setae and a black petiole.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="34.[163,1071,202,560]" pageId="34" pageNumber="417">
D e s c r i p t i o n 
<specimenCount box="[385,406,208,229]" pageId="34" pageNumber="417" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
: 
<quantity box="[423,534,202,224]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.15" metricValueMax="2.3" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="34" pageNumber="417" unit="mm" value="21.5" valueMax="23.0" valueMin="20.0">20-23 mm</quantity>
. Black except petiole, tergum I, gastral segment II and segment III basally red. Gastral apex black, without metallic shine, supra-antennal lamellate projection absent, episternal sulcus extending to anteroventral margin of pleuron, mesothoracic venter not prominent anteriorly, arolia well defined and claws without basal tooth. Clypeus, pronotal lobe laterally, propodeum posterolaterally and propodeal enclosure medially covered with appressed silvery setae; erect setae on head and legs black. Ventral margin of clypeus rounded, without distinct median lobe (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figs 55-65" captionStartId="133.[163,203,1431,1451]" captionTargetBox="[163,1069,204,1407]" captionTargetId="figure-1@133.[163,1070,204,1411]" captionTargetPageId="133" captionText="Figs 55-65: clypeus of female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5341146" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5341146/files/figure.png" pageId="34" pageNumber="417">Fig. 56</figureCitation>
), disk nearly flat. Pronotal collar and scutum sparsely punctate, admedian line distinct. Scutellum punctate on anterior half, longitudinally ridged on posterior half. Propodeal enclosure irregularly rugose and covered with fine appressed silvery setae along midline, distinctly transversely ridged and glabrous laterally. Mesopleuron and metapleuron punctato-rugose. Pronotal collar laterally: 
<figureCitation box="[613,705,510,532]" captionStart="Figs 149-160" captionStartId="141.[163,203,1385,1405]" captionTargetBox="[190,1054,227,1365]" captionTargetId="figure-4@141.[163,1069,728,1365]" captionTargetPageId="141" captionText="Figs 149-160: pronotal collar of female in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5341163" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5341163/files/figure.png" pageId="34" pageNumber="417">Fig. 150</figureCitation>
. Flagellomere I: II=1.6; length of petiole = hindtarsomeres I+0.75×II.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="34.[163,1070,574,652]" pageId="34" pageNumber="417">
The male of 
<taxonomicName box="[297,445,574,596]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Ammophila" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="34" pageNumber="417" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="brevipennis">
<emphasis box="[297,445,574,596]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="417">A. brevipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from the female as follows (
<bibRefCitation author="GUPTA V" box="[819,992,574,596]" pageId="34" pageNumber="417" pagination="23 - 27" refId="ref90209" refString="GUPTA V. K. (1960): Entomological survey of Himalaya. Part 22. Notes of some Hymenoptera (Insecta) collected by the Third Entomological Expedition to the Northwest Himalayas (1956). - Records of the Indian Museum 55: 23 - 27." type="journal article" year="1960">GUPTA 1960: 26</bibRefCitation>
): &quot;head and thorax more densely pilose; shallow furrows on each side of the tegulae indistinct; petiole black in basal half&quot;.
</paragraph>
